lyrics:
2 contributorsshe was born to run lyricsverse 1
she said goodbye to her daddy
while her mamma cried
i kept the motor running
in my car outside

verse 2
through red taillights
and a cloud of dust

it was all about us
sitting on the seat right next to me
we drove with a tank full of destiny

chorus
she was born to run
she was born to run
yeah she was born to run
born to run to me

verse 3
with a new world waiting

with everything we owned
packed in the backseat
we had each other
that was all wed need
see brooks  dunn liveget tickets as low as 30you might also likeverse 4
they all called me crazy
said shed never settle down
i was just her ticket
her ticket out of town

fate proved em wrong
because shes been mine
mine all along

chorus
she was born to run
she was born to run
yeah she was born to run
born to run to me oh i

its been years now

somewhere somehow
wed make through

no two ways about it
